<br>
If the only restriction set on items is &quot;NBG&quot;, then <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> yes</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, a rogue can roll on a high AC shield if he keeps a set of AC armor in a weight reducing bag for the times when he has to act as tank in his cleric/druid heavy guild... and a warrior is entitled to roll on a high int item if he considers himself a professional blacksmith who's tradeskilling would be greatly helped by the boost.  They're not greedy for asking, they can actually use the item in question (even if not as much as someone else could).<br>
<br>
If you don't want the warrior to end up w/ a piece of hybrid armor, or a rogue to end up with a high AC shield, just lay that out in the rules before you start.<br>
<br>
Someone else said it in a different thread, but the best thing you can do is be clear about the loot rules from the start.<br>
