Syll, need is always determined by utility over time for the character or class.  That shield may have all/all written on it, but as far as rolling goes, it should be pal/sk only.  Just like dragon bags are all/all, but are really monk-only as far as awarding (anyone else will just sell it to a monk and buy two tinks).  I've heard every song&amp;dance under the sun about how some character has some particular use that makes them special and thus deserving of rolling on an item that has obvious vastly greater utility for another class or character.  But, that's all it is.  Just singing dancing greed in sheep's clothing.  Well, maybe lamb's clothing.  It's a minor greed.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
BTW, I thought of an amusing way to do open raid loot the other day: put it all in one big pile and permit people to BUY it.  Then distribute the cash amongst all present at the raid; eg. CoF drops.  If you want it, pay the typical 75K market value.  Same for all the loot.  Subtract 'dot costs and then hand out the cash to all raiders.  Every raider would likely walk out with about 3-5k.  Can't afford it?  Do lots of raids, raise cash, buy it then.<br>
<br>
It would sure cut down on greed, too.  It's like a DKP system.  Suddenly you see that all those people whining about being restricted from looting incidental seldom used items better suited for another class are not spending any DKP on those and looting them.  It's &quot;Siffo'ism&quot; all over.  Unwilling to spend his own cash on a nice shield, but if there's a chance at a free one, he's all over it!  Why?  Because it doesn't provide enough utility to him to be worth buying and he knows it.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ..  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usiffo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siffo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silly old Rogue</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/1/02 10:55:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1475.topic&index=65>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: From what you said, Siffo, you don't ..</span><hr size=1> Oh of course you are so right Bjond!<br>
