Edity part: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  I realised that he had never addressed the issue and I was getting side tracked into his little pontificating session instead of answering the question</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usiffo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siffo</A> at: 10/2/02 1:45:48 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utukka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tukka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/02 2:09:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1475.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.atlantic.net/~tukka/glowhand.jpg height=44 width=44></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just answer the question</span><hr size=1> Siffo, I'm sorry if replies subsequent to yours didn't answer your question. Given that this thread was started based on a loot dispute, I don't find it particularly strange or unacceptable that it's turned into a debate on what constitutes a fair loot policy and how a person should treat and interpret NBG loot rules.<br>
<br>
But to attempt to answer your question, I don't think that a 25 AC difference is worth the melee damage you're going to lose as a rogue by giving up your secondary weapon, unless you have a really lame secondary weapon, even if you are tanking.  Rogues make poor tanks overall anyhow, possibly the worst of all the melee classes, especially given the fact that their strength is damage output, and by facing an NPC toe to toe, a rogue is giving up a big portion of what makes him so effective (namely, backstab.)  Not to mention the aggro you are giving up by making fewer attacks.<br>
<br>
If you find yourself in a situation where there is no other tank in the group, it would probably be better to attempt some other strategy than straight tanking.  Fear kiting, or taunt kiting, pet tanking, ect. or try hard to find a warrior, shadow knight, paladin or even ranger or monk to join the group to do the tanking.<br>
<br>
Will a 25 AC boost help you tank?  Of course (though there is a practical AC cap of 1200-1300), but as has been noted, you probably won't notice it without parsing.  The fact that you'll have to tank <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> longer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> due to your loss of dual wield or 2H weapon damage likely will totally offset the advantage you will have in tanking better due to higher AC/HP.<br>
<br>
At least that's how it seems to me. <p><B><FONT FACE="Comic Sans MS">--Tukka</FONT></B><BR>
