I use many forms of strategies to work with unconventional groups. A lot of times I have more AC than any warriors or paladins there and in a lot of places kiting doesnt work do to add cogestion or no one that can snare. If I had alternatives I would be using them but I don't, it is just me the rogue tank and I have to live with it. Then add a mutiple pull where I am trying to keep aggro of a few targets. Because I am the tank for the group I normaly get aggro first and unless they get real lucky in their hits I have to loose it intentionaly to back stab and once I do back stab I have to literaly evade and back out of the locale aggro range to try and get the mob to turn from me and even then the mob will often turn right back to me when I get close.<br>
<br>
So I figure I need to increase my AC and lower my aggro some this should allow me absorb more damge and still use my evade to get backstabs.<br>
<br>
Like I said it is unconventional but then I still solo sometimes at 47 which by common opinion rogues can't do either,<br>
<br>
Maybe it will work maybe it won't since no one seems to have tried it I guess I will have to and see how much difference it makes. That silly shield would have answered the question and if it hadn't worked, well I do know some young paladins that would have used it.<br>
<br>
