I have to say that one of the great things about Saga is the fact that we often have folks fighting in less &quot;ideal&quot; groups and we still do reasonably well.<br>
<br>
Give me an unconventional group anytime over your standard &quot;dream group&quot;.  I find experimentation, uncertainty, and near death experiences much more entertaining than knowing that you and your group have little chance of death.<br>
<br>
Examples of a recent groups:  A bard, two paladins, two druids and a rogue in Kedge.  Fun! Fun! Fun! <br>
