<br>
In general, if you don't know you want it and deserve it over others, don't roll or ask for it unless it's been thrown open as a tradable/sellable.  If you don't want to hear that you've done something greedy, don't ask if something you've done fits that description; ie. don't ask questions in the soapbox when you want reasurances and not answers.  And especially don't go looking for a fight when you don't get the reasurance you wanted.  You'll get beat black and blue. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderating inconsistently<br>since Jun 2002</span><br>  Posts: 1425<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/02 1:27:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1475.topic&index=74>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Eh, Tup ..</span><hr size=1>    If everything you said is true, that the shield would give him no additional benefit in combat, even when fighting monsters ~10 levels lower than him, at best it makes him uninformed, not greedy.  He was planning on using the shield.<br>
