<br>
Whether it's greed or not is all based on how much extra weight you put on your own desire for an item versus how much basic utility the item provides to you and others.  If it provides little utility to you, but you're rolling against those that it has great utility for, that's greed.  When you don't know the utilities, you're just admitting all you have is desire and you aren't considering the utilities at all.  Sure you might be uninformed, but that doesn't make it any less greedy.  It just gives you a nice opening for appologizing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utuppentangledroots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuppen Tangledroots</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.marshall.edu/~parsons6/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/2/02 2:02:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1475.topic&index=76>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.marshall.edu/~parsons6/tupsface.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Eh, Tup ..</span><hr size=1> Thanks for making the point, Syll.<br>
